  "text": "Understanding and effectively capturing peoples' perceptions is difficult [CITATION_1] ) since it involves capturing often intangible views, disentangling perceived cause and effect, and adopting the role of an unbiased yet discerning listener. We use a constructivist approach, which follows that reality is constructed in multiple ways based on social context, location and actions, and perceptions of social actors.",
